        <param>
          <type>bool</type>
          <declname>active</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Signal that application data is actively flowing → CONNECTED (green solid). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Call setLinkActive(true) on each unit of inbound data (<ref refid="namespacePanelBridge" kindref="compound">PanelBridge</ref>: a DCS-BIOS export seen; <ref refid="namespacePanelGroup" kindref="compound">PanelGroup</ref>: a CTRL_BCAST received). The link auto-decays back to NORMAL after ~500 ms with no further calls. CONNECTED is only shown while the CAN bus is healthy; a CAN fault masks it and it re-engages automatically on recovery if data is still flowing.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>active</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>True to (re)assert the data-flowing link; false to drop it immediately. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
